S.M.A.R.T. Monitoring Tools For Windows is an alternate package for smartmontools by Bruce Allen and Christian Franke. 
		</summary>
    <description>
Smartmontools contains utility programs (smartctl, smartd) to control/monitor storage systems using the Self-Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting Technology System (S.M.A.R.T.) built into most modern ATA and SCSI disks.
		
This installer package has been created to quickly install smartd as a service, smartctl for on-demand querying S.M.A.R.T. data, and a MTA for sending alerts to email.  The following software will be installed:
- smartmontools by Bruce Allen and Christian Franke, http://smartmontools.sourceforge.net
- sendemail by Brandon Zehm, http://caspian.dotconf.net
- Mailsend by Muhammad Muquit, http://www.muquit.com
- Inno Setup by Jordan Russel, http://www.jrsoftware.org
- Gzip by Free Software Foundation, Inc. Copyright (C) 1992, 1993 Jean-loup Gailly, http://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/
- Base64 by Matthias GÃ¤rtner, http://www.rtner.de/software/base64.htm
- dd by Chrysocome and John Newbigin, http://www.chrysocome.net/dd

For usage and examples, see https://github.com/deajan/smartmontools-win/blob/master/README-EN.TXT

See 'smartmontools' for installing only command-line tools smartctl and smartd.
See 'GSmartControl' for a GTK GUI interface.
		</description>
